BOOLEAN PdpContext::Accept (  Type  type = NoType,
const Address &  address = Address()
) 
 

Accept a context activation request from the net, using m_id as new context - response should be used within the PdpContextManagerControl::OnActivateContextIndication() method.

BOOLEAN PdpContext::Activate (  const PppFrame &  ppp_frame  ) 
 

Used to send an activation request encoded in a ppp_frame. This request includes automatic user authentication. The only callback invoked afterwards is PdpContextControl::OnActivateCompleted(). Callback PdpContextControl::OnAuthenticateCompleted() is not invoked in this case.

BOOLEAN PdpContext::Connect (  Protocol  protocol  ) 
 

Activates a context and establishes a connection. When connection is successfully established, then the access point id, and the current quality of service are available.

BOOLEAN PdpContext::ReadNegotiatedDnsServerAddress (   ) 
 

Reads the negotiated DNS server address. Note that this method just sends the read request to the stack. The DNS server address itself can be then read within the PdpContextControl::ReadNegotiatedDnsServerAddressCompleted() callback using the PdpContextManager::GetLastNegotiatedDnsServerAddrress() method.

void PdpContext::Reject (   )  [static]
 

Reject a context activation request from the net - response should be used within the PdpContextManagerControl::OnActivateContextIndication() method.

BOOLEAN PdpContext::SetAutomaticDnsServerNegotiation (  BOOLEAN  enable  ) 
 

Enables/disables the automatic DNS server address negotiation functionality. By default this functionality is disabled in stack. Therefore, to be able to read the negotiated DNS server address late on after the PDP context activation, this feature has to be enabled first. Note that enabling or disabling of the automatic DNS server address negotiation has to be done before activating the PDP context.
